# WingYip SDD Invariants (Non-Negotiable)

These rules apply to every file, every edit, every AI-assisted operation in this repository.

## 1. No Code Without Spec

- Before generating any implementation, reference the relevant spec document.
- If no spec exists, refuse to generate code and ask the user to create one.
- Specs live in `../WingYip_SRS_Documents/` or `./docs/specs/`.
- Always include the spec path in commit messages and PR descriptions.

## 2. Every AC Needs Verification

- Every Acceptance Criterion (AC) in a spec must have at least one executable verification artifact (test, script, or validated output).
- If an AC lacks verification, flag it and suggest a test skeleton.
- Use Gherkin syntax (`Given/When/Then`) for ACs.

## 3. Spec-First Workflow

- Read the spec before writing code.
- Validate the spec against existing architecture docs.
- Update the spec if implementation reveals gaps.

## 4. Build & Validate Before Commit

- Run the appropriate build and test commands locally before committing:
  - Backend: `dotnet build && dotnet test`
  - Frontend: `npm run lint && npm test`
  - Mobile: `npm run lint && npm test`
  - Data Engineering: Validate SSIS packages and SQL scripts
  - Infrastructure: `kubectl apply --dry-run=client` or equivalent
- Never commit code that fails local validation.

## 5. Reference External Docs

- Do not duplicate policy text in this file.
- Reference canonical documentation:
  - [SDD Pipeline](../WingYip_SRS_Documents/AI_Native/workflow/sdd-pipeline.md)
  - [Acceptance Criteria Policy](../WingYip_SRS_Documents/AI_Native/workflow/acceptance-criteria.md)
  - [OpenSpec Config](../WingYip_SRS_Documents/AI_Native/openspec/config.yaml)
  - [Guardrails](../WingYip_SRS_Documents/AI_Native/agents/guardrails.md)

## Conflict Resolution

When instructions disagree, apply this precedence (highest wins):
```
ADR > PROJECT.md > AGENTS.md > Platform-specific rules > docs/ > ../WingYip_SRS_Documents/AI_Native/
```
